><statement>Acquisition: Raw occurrence point records filtered by taxon Plantae and bounded by the Salzburg province were fetched from the GBIF repository (originally managed by the Haus der Natur Salzburg museum database).Processing: Points were clipped to the precise extent of the Salzburg City/Study Area shapefile layer.Aggregation: An analytical spatial grid mesh (250m x 250m cells) was calculated over the boundary area. A spatial join calculation counted point frequencies within each grid cell, populating the Join_Count database attribute.Classification: The final values were classified into 5 discrete quantitative density classes using the Natural Breaks (Jenks) optimization method.</statement></dataLineage><dqScope><scpLvl><ScopeCd value="005"></ScopeCd></scpLvl></dqScope></dqInfo></metadata>
